						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of a lamp-stand and of 96 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily in the temple of Mahādēva at Tirumaḻavāḍi in Mīypilārunāḍu a sub-division of Poygai-nāḍu, by <hi rend="bold">Āttiraiyaṉ Śivadāsaṉ Śōlai</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Uttamaśōḻa-Brahmādarāyaṉ of Pūvaṇṇūr</hi> in Veṇṇikkūṟṟam. This is probably an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḻa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
